posts.title: I'm about to turn 55 and today was the first time since I turned 12 I didn't have a job to go to.
posts.content:
Spent the last four months closing my shop/business. Yesterday I turned in the keys. 23 years ago I took $1,000 and started a small business and grew it to a point it had eight employees in 2019. Yesterday I hugged my final employee, started with me at 16 and is 27 now. Most of my workers got their first jobs from me.

I held on as long as I could. In many ways I am excited for what is to come and terrified by what is to come. I honestly probably could take a few years off but I more than likely will start hunting once all the home projects I have put off the last ten years get finished. My wife has a long list.

I have never not had a job, spent the day disconnecting services and getting rid of the last of the garbage. The hardest part was taking 20 years of your life and trailer by trailer dumping it in a landfill and watching your dreams get crushed by a pay loader.

posts.title: I'm about to turn 55 and today was the first time since I turned 12 I didn't have a job to go to.
posts.content:
Spent the last four months closing my shop/business. Yesterday I turned in the keys. 23 years ago I took $1,000 and started a small business and grew it to a point it had eight employees in 2019. Yesterday I hugged my final employee, started with me at 16 and is 27 now. Most of my workers got their first jobs from me.

I held on as long as I could. In many ways I am excited for what is to come and terrified by what is to come. I honestly probably could take a few years off but I more than likely will start hunting once all the home projects I have put off the last ten years get finished. My wife has a long list.

I have never not had a job, spent the day disconnecting services and getting rid of the last of the garbage. The hardest part was taking 20 years of your life and trailer by trailer dumping it in a landfill and watching your dreams get crushed by a pay loader.
